    <svcsubproc>
        <title>Safety Gate</title>
        <para>The front bumper mounted swing arm safety gate is provided on all BE series chassis. The safety gate is
            comprised of three major assemblies: the drive motor which is mounted behind the passenger side of the front
            bumper assembly, the safety gate arm which connects to the drive mechanism and attaches on the outside area
            of the front bumper assembly, and the electro magnetic gate lock, which holds the gate in the closed
            position and is mounted on the front surface of the driver side of the bumper assembly. The safety gate
            assembly can be removed from the bumper assembly without removing the front bumper.
        </para>
        <figure id="f47006155" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/g47006155.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="288px"
                     scalefitheight="288px"/>
            <caption>Figure 155. Safety Gate Motor Mounting Bolts</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. SAFETY GATE MOTOR MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To remove the safety gate drive motor assembly unplug power supply harness (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f47006156">Figure 156, Item 5</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Open the safety gate and locate the gate mounting nuts and bolts on the gate drive arm (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f47006156">Figure 156, Item 2</hotlnk>). Remove the safety gate arm.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f47006156" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/g47006156.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 156. Safety Gate Drive Motor Assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. SAFETY GATE DRIVE ARM</callout1>
                <callout1>2. BUMPER OPENING</callout1>
                <callout1>3. FRONT BUMPER ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                <callout1>4. SAFETY GATE DRIVE MOTOR</callout1>
                <callout1>5. SAFETY GATE HARNESS CONNECTION</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">With safety gate arm removed, locate the four gate drive motor mounting bolts and nuts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f47006157">Figure 157, Item 5</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen and remove the motor mounting bolts.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the drive motor.</para>
        </step1>
        <para>The safety gate is held in place during operation against the front bumper assembly by means of an
            electromagnet lock device (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f47006158">Figure 158, Item 3</hotlnk>). When the ignition is in the on position, the magnet
            on the driver side of the front bumper is activated and secures the bumper at the point where a steel plate
            (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f47006158">Figure 158, Item 4</hotlnk>) is attached to the safety gate arm.
        </para>
        <figure id="f47006157" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/g47006157.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="288px"
                     scalefitheight="288px"/>
            <caption>Figure 157. Safety Gate Assembly</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. SAFETY GATE ARM</callout1>
                <callout1>2. SAFETY GATE ARM MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                <callout1>3. SAFETY GATE DRIVE ARM</callout1>
                <callout1>4. BUMPER ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                <callout1>5. DRIVE MOTOR MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <figure id="f47006158" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/g47006158.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 158. Safety Gate Magnetic Lock</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. SAFETY GATE ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                <callout1>2. BUMPER ASSEMBLY</callout1>
                <callout1>3. ELECTROMAGNET LOCK DEVICE</callout1>
                <callout1>4. SAFETY GATE ARM STEEL PLATE</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To remove locking device disconnect harness connection at rear of bumper assembly.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the electromagnet mounting bolts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f47006159">Figure 159, Item 2</hotlnk>) and loosen from bracket and bumper by removing
                bolts, flat washers and lock nut.
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove lock device and bracket (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f47006159">Figure 159, Item 3 and 4</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f47006159" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic filename="../figg47/g47006159.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="272px"
                     scalefitheight="272px"/>
            <caption>Figure 159. Magnetic Lock Device</caption>
            <calloutgroup>
                <callout1>1. BUMPER MOUNTING BOLT</callout1>
                <callout1>2. MAGNET DEVICE MOUNTING BOLTS</callout1>
                <callout1>3. ELECTROMAGNET FACE</callout1>
                <callout1>4. GATE GUIDE BRACKET</callout1>
            </calloutgroup>
        </figure>
